{"data":{"post":{"html":"<p>Watch my TEDx talk, <em>Is the World Growing Up?</em></p>\n<p>Teenagers have been characterized as being rebellious, in search of their identities, and in a transitioning period of maturity. Most of all, they are expected to grow up. Can we say that the world is in a similar stage of adolescence?</p>\n<p>Given at <a href=\"https://www.ted.com/tedx/events/21762\" title=\"TEDxYouth@UTS Event\">TEDxYouth@UTS</a> on March 29, 2017.<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n  </p>\n<div style=\"position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;padding-top:30px;height:0;overflow:hidden;\">\n  <iframe style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/1aHLtyXbEf8\" parameters=\"rel=0&modestbranding=1&autohide=1\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div>\n&nbsp;  \n&nbsp;  \n&nbsp;  \n&nbsp;  ","frontmatter":{"title":"Is the World Growing Up ?","image":"work/earthrise-ted.jpg","description":"My TEDx Talk discussing this question","date":"2017-03-27"}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/synesthesia/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Synesthesia!"}},"next":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.1639185257032008,"src":"/static/acc37fa82268a2a81ebe97e944c84c2e/8484e/earthrise-ted.jpg","srcSet":"/static/acc37fa82268a2a81ebe97e944c84c2e/6ad16/earthrise-ted.jpg 200w,\n/static/acc37fa82268a2a81ebe97e944c84c2e/8f1ca/earthrise-ted.jpg 400w,\n/static/acc37fa82268a2a81ebe97e944c84c2e/8484e/earthrise-ted.jpg 800w,\n/static/acc37fa82268a2a81ebe97e944c84c2e/150f3/earthrise-ted.jpg 1200w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"pageContext":{"post_slug":"/blog/is-the-world-growing-up/","img_path":"work/earthrise-ted.jpg","prev_slug":"/blog/synesthesia/","next_slug":null}}